# Top 20 Amass Commands for Domain Enumeration and Information Gathering

Amass is a versatile tool for domain enumeration and information gathering. Here are the top 20 commands to help you make the most of its capabilities:

### 1. Basic Domain Enumeration

  
sudo amass enum -d example.com
*Enumerates subdomains of `example.com`.*

### 2. Passive Enumeration

  
sudo amass enum -passive -d example.com
*Conducts passive enumeration without active probing.*

### 3. Active Enumeration

  
sudo amass enum -active -d example.com
*Performs active probing to gather detailed information.*

### 4. Save Output to a File

  
sudo amass enum -d example.com -o output.txt
*Outputs enumeration results to `output.txt`.*

### 5. Brute Force Enumeration

  
sudo amass enum -brute -d example.com
*Performs brute force subdomain enumeration.*

### 6. Use a Custom Wordlist for Brute Force

  
sudo amass enum -brute -d example.com -w wordlist.txt
*Uses `wordlist.txt` for brute force enumeration.*

### 7. Include Additional Data Sources

  
sudo amass enum -src -d example.com
*Uses additional data sources for enumeration.*

### 8. Specify a Configuration File

  
sudo amass enum -config amass_config.ini -d example.com
*Uses settings from `amass_config.ini` for enumeration.*

### 9. Maximize DNS Queries

  
sudo amass enum -d example.com -max-dns-queries 1000
*Sets the maximum number of DNS queries to 1000.*

### 10. Include ASN Information

  
sudo amass enum -d example.com -asn
*Includes ASN (Autonomous System Number) information in the results.*

### 11. Include IP Addresses

  
sudo amass enum -d example.com -ip
*Includes IP addresses of the discovered subdomains.*

### 12. Use Only IPv4 Addresses

  
sudo amass enum -d example.com -ipv4
*Limits the enumeration to IPv4 addresses.*

### 13. Use Only IPv6 Addresses

  
sudo amass enum -d example.com -ipv6
*Limits the enumeration to IPv6 addresses.*

### 14. Use a Specific Resolver

  
sudo amass enum -d example.com -r 8.8.8.8
*Uses the specified DNS resolver (8.8.8.8).*

### 15. Specify Output Format

  
sudo amass enum -d example.com -o output.json
*Outputs results in JSON format.*

### 16. Output in CSV Format

  
sudo amass enum -d example.com -o output.csv
*Outputs results in CSV format.*

### 17. Include Recursive Subdomains

  
sudo amass enum -d example.com -recursive
*Includes recursive subdomain enumeration.*

### 18. Use Verbose Mode

  
sudo amass enum -d example.com -v
*Enables verbose mode for detailed output.*

### 19. Set Maximum Enumeration Time

  
sudo amass enum -d example.com -timeout 10m
*Sets the maximum enumeration time to 10 minutes.*

### 20. Visualize Results

  
sudo amass viz -d example.com -o output.dot
*Outputs enumeration results in Graphviz DOT format.*

---

By utilizing these commands, you can perform comprehensive and detailed domain enumeration using Amass. Adjust the options as needed to fit your specific information-gathering requirements.
